1 A BILL for an Act to amend and reenact section 61-34-04 of North Dakota Century Code,
2 relating to eligibility for the drought disaster livestock water assistance program.
3 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATIVE ASSEMBLY OF NORTH DAKOTA:
4 SECTION 1. AMENDMENT. Section 61-34-04 of the North Dakota Century Code is
5 amended and reenacted as follows:
6 61-34-04. Eligibility - Application for assistance.
7 Applicants with livestock water supply problems caused by drought may apply for
8 assistance from the program. An applicant must first apply for water cost-share assistance from
9 the United States department of agriculture farm service agency. If cost-share assistance is
10 denied by the agency, the applicant may forward the application to the commission for
11 consideration. An application forwarded to the commission must include a document from the
12 United States department of agriculture farm service agency stating the reason for denial of
13 cost-share assistance. The department of water resources shall review all applications received
14 by the commission. Notwithstanding any other provision of law, a water supply project
15 commenced after application for funding is made but without prior approval of the department is
16 eligible for funding consideration from the program. The department shall provide funds for
17 approved applications in accordance with rules and criteria for eligibility and only to the extent
18 that funding is available. A drought disaster livestock water assistance program project located
19 on Indian land is eligible for the program.
